abstract: Brazil's planemaker Embraer S.A. said it is studying the development of a new light military transport plane together with the Brazilian Air Force, the company said in a statement on Thursday.
snippet: Brazil's planemaker Embraer S.A. said it is studying the development of a new light military transport plane together with the Brazilian Air Force, the company said in a statement on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: BRASILIA — Brazil's planemaker Embraer S.A. said it is studying the development of a new light military transport plane together with the Brazilian Air Force, the company said in a statement on Thursday.
headline_main: Brazil's Embraer Plans to Develop New Light Military Transport Plane
headline_print_headline: Brazil's Embraer Plans to Develop New Light Military Transport Plane

abstract: Semiconductor company Mellanox Technologies has received approval from EU antitrust and Mexico for its proposed acquisition by chipmaker Nvidia for $6.8 billion, a regulatory filing showed on Thursday.
snippet: Semiconductor company Mellanox Technologies has received approval from EU antitrust and Mexico for its proposed acquisition by chipmaker Nvidia for $6.8 billion, a regulatory filing showed on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Semiconductor company Mellanox Technologies has received approval from EU antitrust and Mexico for its proposed acquisition by chipmaker Nvidia for $6.8 billion, a regulatory filing showed on Thursday.
headline_main: Nvidia, Mellanox Technologies Win EU Approval for $6.8 Billion Deal
headline_print_headline: Nvidia, Mellanox Technologies Win EU Approval for $6.8 Billion Deal

abstract: Saying neither Joshua Boyle nor Caitlin Coleman, who were held captive for five years in Afghanistan, were credible, a judge dismissed all charges.
snippet: Saying neither Joshua Boyle nor Caitlin Coleman, who were held captive for five years in Afghanistan, were credible, a judge dismissed all charges.
lead_paragraph: OTTAWA — Joshua Boyle, a Canadian held hostage with his American wife in Afghanistan for five years, was cleared on Thursday of charges that he repeatedly abused and assaulted her after their rescue.
